title: VPFL Week 14
author: VD
content_html:
65 Fromunda Cheezheads (11-3)
55 Mounds View Meerkats (6-8)

105 Bradford Gamma Rays (6-8)
81 Greenfield Grizzlies (9-5)

80 RR Redbeards (9-5)
53 Bailout Banksters (6-8)

74 Bane Sidhe (9-5)
59 Mercury Marauders (4-10)

59 Suburban Churchians (6-8)
50 Boot Hill Hangmen (4-10)

Another regular season comes to a close. I’m disappointed to miss the playoffs, but hardly surprised due to the copious injuries my keepers suffered this year. Nate put in what was arguably the best management performance of his career, bringing the Redbeards back with a strong run to make the playoffs, while the Grizzlies started strong and faded.  Fromundah took the regular season title with the weakest 2-game lead we’ve yet seen; four teams scored more points, including two teams who finished five games behind them.

As always, luck plays its part. The first round:

Greenfield hosts the defending champion Sidhe and Fromundah is home to the Redbeards.
